            Algeria – July 5, 1962
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image
          border-radius="10px"
          padding="10px 12px"
          width="600px"
          src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/algerian-independence-repatriation-1962.jpg"
          alt="French citizens repatriated from Algeria arrive in Marseille following Algeria’s independence in 1962."
          href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com"
        />

        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i
              >French citizens (pieds-noirs) repatriated from Algeria arrive in
              Marseille in July 1962, following the end of the Algerian War and
              Algeria’s independence. Credits: Getty Images/Keystone-France</i
            >
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Algeria’s independence from France followed one of the most violent
            liberation struggles of the 20th century. The
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-jul-25-iatw-h3-5-algerian-war"
              target="_blank"
              >Algerian War</a
            >
            (1954-1962) led to the deaths of over a million people. France
            finally recognized Algerian sovereignty after a referendum in March
            1962.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>(not so) Fun fact:</strong> After independence, nearly a
            million French settlers, known as
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-jul-25-iatw-h3-6-pieds-noirs"
              target="_blank"
              >pieds-noirs</a
            >
            (literally: black feet), fled Algeria in one of the largest mass
            exoduses of modern European history.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
