            Poland – November 11, 1918 & June 1989
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image
          border-radius="10px"
          padding="10px 12px"
          width="600px"
          src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/poland-independence-march-2021.jpg"
          alt="Large crowd waves Polish flags during a National Independence Day march in Warsaw on November 11, 2021."
          href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com"
        />

        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i
              >Demonstrators wave Polish flags during a march celebrating
              National Independence Day in Warsaw, Poland, on November 11, 2021.
              Credits: Dawid Zuchowicz/Agencja Wyborcza via Reuters</i
            >
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Poland is one of the few countries to celebrate two major
            independence moments: 1918 (from partition) and 1989 (from
            communism). They gained independence after 123 years of being
            partitioned between Russia, Prussia, and Austria. The date coincides
            with the
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-5-jul-25-iatw-h5-9-end-of-world-war-i"
              target="_blank"
              >end of World War I</a
            >, when the map of Europe was redrawn. Since then, Poland’s
            independence has been interrupted multiple times, by Nazi occupation
            during World War II and Soviet control afterward. The Solidarity
            movement in 1989 sparked Poland’s second rebirth, this time as a
            democratic republic.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
